page.title: 14Some Local Wildlife
page.content: {Red squirrels -}some are almost black, live in the trees by Gatcombe Church - seen gathering beech mast in autumn. Numbers of{foxes and badgers}are found throughout the area,{hedgehogs}are common,{rabbits}are numerous. {Butterflies}congregate on the Downs around Tolt -{Small Tortoise Shell, {Meadow Brown, Comma. } {Barn Owls}live near Sheat Manor,{Green {Woodpeckers}frequent Gatcombe Valley {Black and White Woodpeckers}by Sheat.{ {The Canada Goose}is now breeding on the drainage reservoirs (Medina). {Cowslips}grow on the unploughed area near Tolt Copse, followed by{Early {Purple, Bee and Spider Orchids.}Many } common wild flowers bloom on verges and in copses.{Wild hops}grow along the disused railway by Blackwater. {The Evening Primrose}is still found on St. George's Down.
